HEADWORD: Greediness
<hw>Greed"i*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS
<ets>gr⟦aemac⟧dignes</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being greedy;
vehement and selfish desire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fox in stealth, wolf in <qex>greediness.</qex></q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Ravenousness; voracity; eagerness;
avidity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greedy</ent>⟦br⟧
